J@rv1s ran these down this afternoon. Go straight to building.
A. Kalshi API — P1 Cache Fix Field Names
Field confirmed: `expected_expiration_time`
From Kalshi docs: "expected_expiration_time is the time the event
is likely to resolve — for a sports game, typically a few hours
after the scheduled start. close_time is when the market
automatically closes for trading, and may be set well into the
future to allow for rescheduling. That means
expected_expiration_time can be earlier than close_time."
This is exactly why status-only filtering fails — a Spurs
championship market can have close_time in the future while the
event resolved days ago.
ALSO NOTE: GET /events status filter matches on CHILD market
statuses, not event-level status. Filter at the market level,
not event level, for the P1 fix.
B. Polymarket Gamma API — No Auth Required
Base URL: https://gamma-api.polymarket.com
No authentication, no API key, no wallet needed.
Rate limit: ~10 requests/second on public endpoints.
Python pattern (copy-paste ready):
```python
import requests
response = requests.get(
    "https://gamma-api.polymarket.com/markets",
    params={
        "active": "true",
        "limit": 100,
        "order": "volume24hr",
        "ascending": "false"
    }
)
markets = response.json()
# Each market has: question, outcomePrices, volume24hr, liquidity
```
For cross-platform divergence: search by keyword matching the
Kalshi market description, pull outcomePrices (YES implied
probability), compare to Kalshi yes_price. Flag divergences
above threshold as confidence amplifiers.
C. ClubElo API — Free, No Auth, Three Endpoints
Base URL: http://api.clubelo.com
Completely free, no authentication, returns CSV.
Three endpoints:
api.clubelo.com/YYYY-MM-DD → all club ratings as of that date
api.clubelo.com/CLUBNAME → full Elo history for one club
(e.g. api.clubelo.com/ManCity, api.clubelo.com/Arsenal)
api.clubelo.com/fixtures → upcoming fixtures with Elo ratings
Python pattern for daily lambda refresh:
```python
import requests
import pandas as pd
from datetime import date

today = date.today().strftime("%Y-%m-%d")
response = requests.get(f"http://api.clubelo.com/{today}")
# Returns CSV: Rank,Prev,Club,Country,Level,Elo,From,To
df = pd.read_csv(pd.io.common.StringIO(response.text))
# df now has current Elo rating for every tracked club
```
One API call per pipeline run gets current Elo for all clubs.
Dramatically better than FIFA rankings — updated after every
match, accounts for competition weight, covers 1500+ clubs.
NOTE: ClubElo covers club football only. For World Cup national
teams, use eloratings.net — same concept, free access.
