P1 CACHE FIX — THREE-LAYER IMPLEMENTATION
Stale Spurs/Thunder/April payrolls signals still in today's
alert despite last night's fix. Root cause confirmed: price cache
isn't refreshing for resolved markets. Cached entries don't have
the status field → P1 filter finds no status → defaults to
active → passes through.
THREE LAYERS TO BUILD TONIGHT:
Layer 1 (already built): Status filter — exclude markets where
status is 'settled' or 'closed'. Necessary but insufficient.
Layer 2 (NEW): expected_expiration_time check.
Capture this field in price_fetcher.py (confirmed in API
response). If expected_expiration_time is more than 24 hours
in the past → exclude regardless of status field.
Layer 3 (belt-and-suspenders): Price sanity check.
If cached YES price is >95c or <5c → market almost certainly
resolved. Flag for exclusion or force fresh API call.
CACHE TTL (root structural fix): Any cached price older than 12
hours should trigger a fresh API call. Without TTL, the cache
will continue serving stale prices regardless of other layers.
Verification: Thursday morning alert should be clean.
If stale markets still appear Thursday → flag immediately.
